# Legacy Cursor rules entrypoint
# Canonical rules are defined in: .cursor/rules/react-spreadsheet.mdc

- Always follow .cursor/rules/react-spreadsheet.mdc as the source of truth.
- Enforce Node-based component structure under src/components.
- Keep all source code under src/ and update export chains via index.ts.
- Require JSDoc on all public exports and keep changes atomic/scope-limited.
- Write JSDoc in Korean with detailed tags (`@param`, `@returns`, `@throws`, `@example` when needed).
- Add/maintain folder-level tests for logic module changes.
- Manage literal type candidates in `const.ts` as static constants, and derive types from those constants.
- Prefer `const.ts` constants in runtime branch comparisons (avoid raw string literals).
- Keep architecture docs synced when module boundaries/relations change.
- Run `test:run -> typecheck -> build -> pack:check` before publish-related updates.
